   <talk_paragraph index="n1835_conscience_pope-1" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n1835_conscience_pope-1-a" mid="10" select_type="0"><![CDATA[<html>It's nothing.</html>]]></talk_answer>
      <talk_question mid="9"><![CDATA[<html>$Honest Merchant Pero$<BR>You surely are the hero from Lagendia. You're kind enough to accept even the seemingly troublesome tasks. </html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n1835_conscience_pope-1-a" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n1835_conscience_pope-1-b" mid="12" select_type="0"><![CDATA[<html>(Continue)</html>]]></talk_answer>
      <talk_question mid="11"><![CDATA[<html>$Honest Merchant Pero$<BR>I'll tell you more about the kingdom then. Though the exact history of the kingdom is unknown, it is said to have been founded quite a long time ago according to a legend I heard from the kingdom's merchant.</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n1835_conscience_pope-1-b" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n1835_conscience_pope-1-c" mid="14" select_type="0"><![CDATA[<html>(Continue)</html>]]></talk_answer>
      <talk_question mid="13"><![CDATA[<html>$Honest Merchant Pero$<BR>The kingdom obeyed the goddess at first but a Child who came to oversee the area started making unreasonable requests. The king complied at first and gave crops, land, and eventually, people too.</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n1835_conscience_pope-1-c" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n1835_conscience_pope-1-d" mid="16" select_type="0"><![CDATA[<html>What happened next? </html>]]></talk_answer>
      <talk_question mid="15"><![CDATA[<html>$Honest Merchant Pero$<BR>As time passed, it was hard to keep up with the extravagant demands and the king knelt before the Child and begged for mercy. But the Child didn't listen. Stating that it would be going against the goddess if the requests were not met, the Child asked for even more things.</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n1835_conscience_pope-1-d" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n1835_conscience_pope-1-e" mid="18" select_type="0"><![CDATA[<html>Nothing?</html>]]></talk_answer>
      <talk_question mid="17"><![CDATA[<html>$Honest Merchant Pero$<BR>Left with no other choice, the king promised the tributes. A few days later, the promised deadline had arrived but the tributes were nowhere in sight. The furious Child stormed to the kingdom but he found nothing.</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n1835_conscience_pope-1-e" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n1835_conscience_pope-1-f" mid="20" select_type="0"><![CDATA[<html>Where did they go?</html>]]></talk_answer>
      <talk_question mid="19"><![CDATA[<html>$Honest Merchant Pero$<BR>Not even a single crop could be found where the kingdom used to be. It was as if there was nothing there from the beginning. The Child searched the entire area, but couldn't find anyone there, not even the livestock.</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n1835_conscience_pope-1-f" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n1835_conscience_pope-1-g" mid="22" select_type="0"><![CDATA[<html>I see.</html>]]></talk_answer>
      <talk_question mid="21"><![CDATA[<html>$Honest Merchant Pero$<BR>No one knows. That was the day when the kingdom was last seen but it still continues to exist somewhere in the world. The merchant who told me about this also didn't reveal the exact location.</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n1835_conscience_pope-1-g" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n1835_conscience_pope-2" mid="24" select_type="0"><![CDATA[<html>I see.</html>]]></talk_answer>
      <talk_question mid="23"><![CDATA[<html>$Honest Merchant Pero$<BR>It's only a legend. No one knows if it's true.</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n1835_conscience_pope-2" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="" center_image="">
      <talk_question mid="25"><![CDATA[<html>$Honest Merchant Pero$<BR>Please go and see if there are any secret areas that are hidden from sight. <BR><FONT color=#7e12d2>(Go to Secret Seabed Cave)</FONT></html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n1835_conscience_pope-3" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n1835_conscience_pope-3-a" mid="27" select_type="0"><![CDATA[<html>(Tell him about Secret Seabed Cave.)</html>]]></talk_answer>
      <talk_question mid="26"><![CDATA[<html>$Honest Merchant Pero$<BR>You're back. Have you found any secret areas?</html>]]></talk_question>
   </talk_paragraph>
   <talk_paragraph index="n1835_conscience_pope-3-a" image="" itemindex="" portrait_left="" portrait_right="" center_image="">
      <talk_answer link_index="n1835_conscience_pope-3-b" mid="29" select_type="0"><![CDATA[<html>(Continue) </html>]]></talk_answer>
      <talk_question mid="28"><![CDATA[<html>$Honest Merchant Pero$<BR>I see. Then maybe the kingdom exists inside a similar cave too.</html>]]></talk_question>
